QUESTION 5: Write a Python program using SciPy to:
Calculate mean using scipy.stats
Perform a t-test on a sample dataset

from scipy import stats

data1 = [10, 12, 14, 16, 18]
data2 = [11, 13, 15, 17, 19]

mean_value = stats.tmean(data1)
print("Mean:", mean_value)

t_stat, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(data1, data2)

print("T-statistic:", t_stat)
print("P-value:", p_value)


OUTPUT:
Mean: 14.0
T-statistic: -0.5
P-value: 0.6305360755569764

